<Document xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
   id="ID.00002"
  >
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00005"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00006"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The following examples are derived from 
   <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00007"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Homology manifold bordism
   </Em>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> by Heather Johnston and Andrew Ranicki (Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. 352 no 11 (2000), PII: S 0002-9947(00)02630-1).
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00008"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00009"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00010"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00011"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The results of Johnston [?Jo] on homology manifolds are extended here. It is not possible to investigate transversality by geometric methods—as in [?Jo] we employ bordism and surgery instead.
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00012"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00013"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The proof of transversality is indirect, relying heavily on surgery theory—see Kirby and Siebenmann [?KS, III, §1], Marin [?M] and Quinn [?Q3]. We shall use the formulation in terms of topological block bundles of Rourke and Sanderson [?RS].
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00014"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00015"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00016"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile1.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Q
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> is a codimension 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00017"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile2.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>q
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> subspace by Theorem 4.9 of Rourke and Sanderson [?RS]. (Hughes, Taylor and Williams [?HTW] obtained a topological regular neigh­borhood theorem for arbitrary submanifolds ….)
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00018"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00019"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Wall [?Wa, Chapter 11] obtained a codimension 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00020"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile3.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>q
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> splitting obstruction ….
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00021"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00022"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… following the work of Cohen [?Co] on 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00023"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile4.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>PL
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> manifold transversality.
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00024"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00025"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>In this case each inverse image is automatically a 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00026"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile5.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>PL
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> submanifold of codi­mension 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00027"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile6.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>σ
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (Cohen [?Co]), so there is no need to use 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00028"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile7.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>s
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>-cobordisms.
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00029"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00030"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Quinn [?Q2, 1.1] proved that …
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <theorem-like xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00031"
    rolemaps-to="Sect"
   >
  <Caption xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
     id="ID.00032"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Theorem 
   <Lbl xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00033"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>3.1
   </Lbl>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (The additive structure of homology manifold bordism, Johnston [?Jo])
  </Caption>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00034"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00035"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> …
   </text>
  </text-unit>
 </theorem-like>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00036"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00037"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>For 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00038"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile8.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>m≥5
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> the Novikov-Wall surgery theory for topological manifolds gives an exact sequence (Wall [?Wa, Chapter 10].
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00039"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00040"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The surgery theory of topological manifolds was extended to homology man­ifolds in Quinn [?Q1, ?Q2] and Bryant, Ferry, Mio and Weinberger [?BFMW].
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00041"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00042"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>The 4-periodic obstruction is equivalent to an 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00043"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile9.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>m
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>-dimensional homology man­ifold, by [?BFMW].
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00044"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00045"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Thus, the surgery exact sequence of [?BFMW] does not follow Wall [?Wa] in relating homology manifold structures and normal invariants.
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00046"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00047"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>… the canonical 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00048"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile10.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>TOP
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> reduction ([?FP]) of the Spivak normal fibration of 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00049"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile11.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>M
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>…
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <theorem-like xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00050"
    rolemaps-to="Sect"
   >
  <Caption xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
     id="ID.00051"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Theorem 
   <Lbl xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00052"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>3.2
   </Lbl>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> (Johnston [?Jo])
  </Caption>
  <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00053"
     rolemaps-to="Part"
    >
   <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
      id="ID.00054"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
      rolemaps-to="P"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> …
   </text>
  </text-unit>
 </theorem-like>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00055"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00056"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>Actually [?Jo, (5.2)] is for 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00057"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile12.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>m≥7
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>, but we can improve to 
   <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
      id="ID.00058"
      title="math"
      af="tag-AFfile13.tex"
      xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
      Layout:Placement="Inline"
     >
    <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>m≥6
   </Formula>
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?> by a slight variation of the proof as described below.
  </text>
 </text-unit>
 <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
    id="ID.00059"
    rolemaps-to="Part"
   >
  <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
     id="ID.00060"
     xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
     Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
     rolemaps-to="P"
    >
   <?MarkedContent page="1" ?>(This type of surgery on a Poincaré space is in the tradition of Lowell Jones [?Jn].)
  </text>
 </text-unit>
</Document>
